<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>Students who make a score of three or higher on the Advanced Placement test will be given credit for the course at East Central Community College.  Generally an AP score of three will result in awarding three semester hours credit in the subject area.  More than three semester hours credit may be awarded for AP scores of four or five when approved by the appropriate division chairs working in conjunction with departmental faculty and the Vice President for Instruction.</i>
